Good. Now let me fix `ArmClientOptions.cs` and `ArmEnvironment.cs`. 

For `ArmClientOptions.cs`, the JSON structure is:
```json
{
  "resource-manager": {
    "Microsoft.Namespace": {
      "2020-09-01": [
        { "resourceType": "someType" }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

The code deserializes into `Dictionary<string, Dictionary<string, JsonElement>>`, then accesses `allProfile["resource-manager"]` which is a `Dictionary<string, JsonElement>`, then for each entry calls `element.EnumerateObject()` on the `JsonElement` value.


Actually, looking at the type structure again—the outer dictionary has keys like "resource-manager", the inner dictionary has keys like "Microsoft.Namespace", and the values are `JsonElement` objects representing JSON structures. When I call `EnumerateObject()` on those elements, I'm iterating through the properties of those JSON objects. I can simplify this whole approach by using `JsonDocument.Parse` directly...

Parsing the JSON document...

